Imo State Governor, Hope Uzodimma is set to commis­sion a two-kilometre road in new Owerri constructed by Prince Alex Mbata. Daily Independent gath­ered that the road, a dual car­riage with street lights has been named as Prince Alex Mbata road with the approval of the Governor. A source said Governor Uzodimma expressed delight at the gesture of the Lagos based business mogul, Prince Mbata on the construction of the road as a way of helping in the provision of infrastruc­tures and fast track the devel­opment of the state. HOW NIGERIAN MEN CAN NOW NATURALLY STOP PREMATURE EJACULATION, LOW SPERM COUNT AND OTHER MEN'S SEXUAL NEEDS. MADAM ALWAYS WANTS IT BIGGER, STRONGER AND LONG-LASTING!!! Mbata had before now ex­tended the same kind gesture to the people of Ngwoma, Obube community in Ower­ri North Local Government Area with the construction of a 5 km asphalt road with drainage that runs from Ulak­wo to Ngwoma. Besides, the businessman was said to have also built places of worship for his people amongst other philan­thropic gestures. Julius Berger Accomplishes Record Project Deliveries In Port Harcourt Parliamentary Staff Overwhelm NASS Security, Demand Financial Autonomy For State Legislature It would be noted that the 2 km road constructed in Ower­ri would be the first of its kind in Imo state. The Prince Alex Mbata road project is coming at a time when the state govern­ment is making efforts to re­constructing some roads in the state.